sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as Client (Browser)
    participant KAP as kube-auth-proxy<br/>4180/TCP HTTP
    participant OIDC as OIDC Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OAuthSrv as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OSAPI as OpenShift API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Upstream as Upstream Application<br/>HTTP plaintext

    Note over Browser, Upstream: Flow 1: OIDC Authentication (auth mode)
    Browser->>KAP: GET / (no session)<br/>HTTP/4180
    KAP-->>Browser: 302 Redirect to OIDC Provider
    Browser->>OIDC: Authenticate with user credentials<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    OIDC-->>Browser: 302 Redirect with auth code
    Browser->>KAP: GET /oauth2/callback?code=...<br/>HTTP/4180
    KAP->>OIDC: Token exchange<br/>Client credentials + auth code<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    OIDC-->>KAP: Access token + ID token
    KAP-->>Browser: 302 Redirect + Set-Cookie (session)
    Browser->>KAP: GET / (with session cookie)<br/>HTTP/4180
    KAP->>Upstream: Proxied request<br/>X-Forwarded-User, X-Forwarded-Email headers

    Note over Browser, Upstream: Flow 2: OpenShift OAuth Authentication (auth mode)
    KAP->>OAuthSrv: OIDC Discovery<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    Browser->>KAP: GET / (no session)<br/>HTTP/4180
    KAP-->>Browser: 302 Redirect to OpenShift OAuth
    Browser->>OAuthSrv: Authenticate with user credentials<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    OAuthSrv-->>Browser: 302 Redirect with auth code
    Browser->>KAP: GET /oauth2/callback?code=...<br/>HTTP/4180
    KAP->>OAuthSrv: Token exchange<br/>Client credentials + auth code<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    OAuthSrv-->>KAP: Access token
    KAP->>OSAPI: GET /apis/user.openshift.io/v1/users/~<br/>Bearer Token<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    OSAPI-->>KAP: User identity info
    KAP->>Upstream: Proxied request<br/>X-Forwarded-User headers

    Note over Browser, Upstream: Flow 3: Envoy ext_authz Check (auth mode)
    participant Envoy as Envoy Proxy
    Envoy->>KAP: GET /oauth2/auth<br/>Forwarded cookies/headers<br/>HTTP/4180
    KAP-->>Envoy: 202 Accepted (authenticated)<br/>or 401 Unauthorized

    Note over Browser, Upstream: Flow 4: Kubernetes RBAC Proxy (rbac mode)
    participant KRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Browser->>KRBAC: Request with Bearer Token<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS 1.2+
    KRBAC->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>ServiceAccount Token<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>KRBAC: Allowed/Denied
    KRBAC->>Upstream: Proxied request (pre-authorized)<br/>HTTP plaintext
